# Security

## Token Storage — EncryptedDataStore Only
```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD — encrypted with Android Keystore
val encryptedPrefs = EncryptedSharedPreferences.create(...)

// ❌ BAD — plaintext storage
getSharedPreferences("prefs", MODE_PRIVATE).edit().putString("token", token)
```
Never store tokens in plain DataStore, SharedPreferences, or files.

## Phone Number Privacy
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD — show phone before confirmation
Text(text = ride.driverPhone)

// ✅ GOOD — gate on confirmed status
if (ride.status == RideStatus.CONFIRMED) {
    Text(text = ride.driverPhone)
    CallButton(phone = ride.driverPhone)
}
```
The `driverPhone` / `userPhone` fields in domain models are nullable — the backend returns `null` before confirmation.

## No PII in Logs
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
Log.d("Auth", "Login attempt for phone=$phone")

// ✅ GOOD
Log.d("Auth", "Login attempt for user=${userId.take(8)}...")
```
Never log full phone numbers, emails, passwords, or tokens in any build variant.

## No Hardcoded Secrets
```kotlin
// ❌ BAD
const val API_BASE_URL = "https://api.sharewind.vn"  // in code
const val FCM_SERVER_KEY = "AAAA..."

// ✅ GOOD — use BuildConfig or remote config
val baseUrl = BuildConfig.API_BASE_URL
```
API base URLs and keys come from `buildConfigField` in `build.gradle.kts`, not source code.

## google-services.json
`google-services.json` is **never committed**. Each developer and CI environment provides their own copy. It is listed in `.gitignore`.

## Certificate Pinning (production)
Add OkHttp `CertificatePinner` for production builds targeting the ShareWind API domain.
